# Secrets & Environment Variables

- **NEVER** put API keys, tokens, or secrets in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables or client-side code
- **NEVER** commit real keys — `.env*.local` is gitignored; `.env.example` uses empty placeholders only
- **NEVER** log full env dumps or `Authorization` headers — redact token-like fields
- Server env vars are read **only** in Route Handlers and `server-only` modules
- Error responses to clients must not contain secrets or internal topology details
- When adding env vars, update `.env.example` with name + one-line purpose
